<TEXT>
   Police in riot gear arrested at least 11
people Friday night when protesters in a ``bash the rich''
demonstration threw rocks and smoke bombs at passing cars. No
injuries were reported.
   About 200 people, many calling themselves anarchists,
demonstrated in the city's Uptown area to call for an end of
wealth, pornography and corporate exploitation. Organizers called
the action a ``bash the rich'' protest.
