<2ND_LINE>AM-Screen Extras,0135</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Screen Extras Guild OKs 3-Year Pact</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The 4,500-member Screen Extras Guild
has approved a three-year contract with the producers of TV
commercials, a spokesman announced Friday.
   Members voted 1,633 to 81 to accept the contract, said Paul
Antico, a member of the SEG board of directors.
   In March SEG members staged a four-week walkout against
producers of television commercials, advertising agencies and
advertisers who wanted to cut the actors' $232.37 daily rate in
half, Antico said.
   The new contract preserves the daily rate and also provides a
slight raise for hand models and a wardrobe allowance for other
actors. The union did accept language that will slightly cut the
number of guild members that producers are required to hire on a
given project, Antico said.
