<HEAD>Quotes From The Presidential Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments Friday from the
presidential campaign trail:
   
   JESSE JACKSON, assuring smaller crowds that greeted him as he
campaigned in Montana that he was as concerned about them as he was
about the larger groups that he had met earlier in the campaign:
``We cannot measure human beings and their needs just by their
political capital. ... It's their humanity that's at stake.''
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, saying his wife who is recovering from delicate
back surgery won't join him when he resumes campaigning for
Tuesday's final four primaries: ``I talked to Kitty in the recovery
room and she said she wanted an ice cream and a massage. I'm
prepared to provide both. ... She certainly is not going to be able
to do any serious campaigning for a while.''
   
   GEORGE BUSH, saluting President Reagan on his return from the
Moscow summit: ``This week, an American president strode the hard
ground of Red Square and reminded the world through the sureness of
his step and the lilting of his words ... what a moving and bracing
thing freedom is. The fact is, you made us proud.''
