<FILEID>AP-NR-06-04-88 0639EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a BC-Quotes     06-04 0128</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Quotes,0133</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Current Quotations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``You have to be willing to work against the odds, to swim
against the current.'' _ Secretary of State George P. Shultz,
describing his new Middle East peace mission.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``We're looking at a very ugly situation. Our animals are very
skinny and a lot have died.'' _ Teofilo Anchondo, a farmer and
cattle producer on a communal farm in Chihuahua, Mexico, who lost
eight of his 50 cows to drought in recent weeks.
