<HEAD>Eight Rebels Killed In Two Clashes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAGAYAN DE ORO, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Government troops killed
eight communist rebels in two encounters with them on the southern
island of Mindanao, military officials said today.
   Col. Rogelio Villanueva of the Philippine Army's 4th Infantry
Division said troops intercepted a group of 20 rebels fleeing
another military operation in Agusan del Norte province on Friday
and killed five of them.
   He said two government militiamen were wounded in the 35-minute
battle near the town of Buenavista, 60 miles from here and 500
miles southeast of Manila.
   In Misamis Oriental province, three guerrillas were killed in a
skirmish Friday that began when soldiers on patrol caught five
rebels collecting ``taxes'' in Lagonglong, a military report said.
One soldier was wounded in the clash, it added.
   Rebels frequently extort cash payments from peasants.
