<TEXT>
   A coalition of clerics led by Southern Christian
Leadership Conference President Joseph Lowery praised the Moscow
summit meeting, but said they wanted to meet with President Reagan
to discuss policies on South Africa.
   The group watched the meeting this week between Reagan and
Soviet leader Mikhail Gorbachev, Lowery, an Atlanta minister, told
