<HEAD>Grown Children Of MIAs Seek Meeting With Reagan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four adults whose fathers are American
servicemen missing in Southeast Asia say they were outraged that
President Reagan expressed willingness to help recover Soviet
soldiers missing from Afghanistan when he has ignored their pleas
for assistance.
   Elizabeth Stewart, Washington representative of the American
League of Families of Prisoners of War in Laos went to the White
House Friday seeking a meeting with Reagan or a representative of
the president to discuss the issue.
