<2ND_LINE>PM-Nigeria-Crash,0181</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Air Force MiG Crashes Into Police Barracks, Killing Pilot And
Policemen</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Nigerian air force MiG crashed into a
police barracks near an air base and killed 12 people, including
the pilot, the military said today.
   Newspapers said at least 21 others were badly burned.
   The air force's logistics command said the Soviet-made fighter
plane crashed into the administrative building of the Nigeria
Police ``C'' division in Makurdi on Friday night.
   The pilot, six policemen, and several civilians died, the
command said in a statement. The civilians had come to the station
to file complaints, it said.
   The statement did not give any other details.
   The 30-year-old plane burst into flames near the city of Makurdi
before crashing, the newspapers said. They said more than 20 other
policemen and a child were badly burned.
   A major air base is located at Makurdi, 370 miles northeast of
Lagos.
   No other details were immediately available.
   Nigeria's air force has at least two versions of the MiG-21.
