<1ST_LINE>r a AM-ToplessChurch     06-04 0159</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Topless Church,0164</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Thieves Give Church Members Clear View Of The Heavens</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANSFIELD, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   When members of the Oak Grove Double
Churches look to the heavens for guidance, they have a clear view.
   Somebody stole their roof.
   Jessie Gobert Jr., 22, of Oxford, was arrested at his home Friday
and charged with the theft, said Capt. Marvin Melton of the DeSoto
Parish Sheriff's Department.
   Church members discovered the tin roof was gone a week ago.
Melton said Gobert and two as-yet-unidentified accomplices are
suspected of selling it for scrap metal.
   He said deputies have found parts of the roof at area scrap
companies, ``but the metal was too badly damaged to recover.''
Meanwhile, he said, the tiny rural church is topless.
   Lt. Charlie Frazier, an investigator in the case, said it changes
the concept of theft.
   ``We used to say that they stole everything that wasn't nailed
down,'' he said. ``Well, that roof was nailed down.''
