Nations flew in and out of the embattled northern Somalia town of
Haregeisa on Saturday to evacuate 160 foreigners stranded there.
   Diplomats said 20 Americans were among the foreigners, most
employed by relief or development agencies, caught in a battle for
the town between rebels and government forces.
