the foreigners from Hargeisa, 600 miles north of Mogadishu, to
Garowe. From Garowe, thet were to be taken to the capital by air or
road.
   The airlift began Friday, three days after rebels of the Somali
National Movement claimed to have captured Hargeisa, and officials
said 83 foreigners were taken out Friday. The rebels have been
fighting to overthrow the government for seven years.
