<HEAD>Safe Bus Driver Has Accident En Route to Awards Ceremony</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A school bus driver en route to an awards ceremony
to get a safe-driving award, turned a corner too sharply and
overturned the bus carrying 29 other school bus drivers.
   Lillie Baltrip and 16 of her passengers went to the hospital
after the accident, but no one was seriously injured, said Larry
Yawn, a spokesman for the Houston Independent School District.
   Superintendent Joan Raymond noted the irony of the timing but
otherwise was not amused. ``There is nothing funny about it,'' she
said.
   In light of recent accidents involving school buses, Ms. Raymond
said the district will give more effort to retraining bus drivers
and monitoring driver performance.
