<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BRF--SubwayAttack     06-04 0155</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Subway Attack,0158</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Token Clerk Killed in Robbery Try</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A subway clerk died Saturday night after she was
severely burned in a failed attempt to rob her token booth,
authorities said.
   The 39-year-old mother of three, Mona Pierre, was burned over 80
percent of her body Friday by an assailant who became angered
because she refused to open her locked, bullet-proof booth.
   He poured a flammable liquid through the small opening in the
booth through which the attendant and the customer exchange money
and tokens, said transit police spokesman Al O'Leary.
   The subsequent fiery blast scorched the token booth and the
suspect fled empty-handed, O'Leary said.
   Ms. Pierre, on the job less than a year, ran from the booth, her
clothes afire. A passenger who had left the station returned when he
heard the explosion and used his sweat shirt to put out the flames
burning Ms. Pierre, O'Leary said.
</TEXT>
