<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BRF--BoulderKilling     06-04 0146</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Boulder Killing,140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Maryland Man Killed When Boulder Crashes Through Windshield</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAKOMA PARK, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 27-year-old Maryland man was killed
when a 36-pound boulder was dropped from a parkway overpass and
crashed through the windshield of his car, police said Saturday.
   Takoma Park Police and the Maryland National Capital Park police
were searching for a young man who reportedly was seen standing on
the bridge overlooking the parkway shortly before the boulder was
dropped on Friday night.
   Police also were searching for several witnesses who saw the
accident and might be able to identify the young man.
   Police identified the dead man as German Rodriguez, who lived in
Takoma Park not far from the scene of the accident. Rodriguez was
taken to an area hospital where he was pronounced dead.
   Police said a passenger in the car, Helen Lopez, was not
seriously injured.
</TEXT>
