<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Beached Cocaine,0103</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Walker Finds Cocaine on Beach</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SALTDEAN, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man walking on a south coast beach
Saturday stumbled on 22 pounds of cocaine, worth as much as $7
million, washed up on the sand in small packages, a Customs
spokesman said.
   The man, whose identity was not immediately revealed, gave police
the 11 one-kilo (2.2 lb) packets that were found at Saltdean, near
Brighton, on the English Channel, authorities said.
   Investigators think the drug may have been discarded by smugglers
at sea. Police were watching the beach in case any more of the drug
washes up.
