<TEXT>
   Here are some commodity price trends for the past week:
   Grain and soybean futures moved sharply higher on the Chicago
Board of Trade.
   Wheat for delivery in July settled Friday at $3.62} a bushel
compared with $3.39{ a week earlier; July corn advanced to $2.34{ a
bushel from $2.16{; July oats rose to $1.96{ a bushel from $1.72};
and July soybeans finished the week at $8.49 a bushel compared with
$7.68.
   Livestock and meat futures were mixed on the Chicago Mercantile
Exchange.
   June live cattle rose to 72.65 cents a pound from 71.92 cents;
August feeder cattle dropped to 75.92 cents a pound from 76.22
cents; June live hogs retreated to 52.45 cents a pound from 53.62
cents; and July frozen pork bellies were at 55.55 cents a pound
compared with 54.32 cents.
