Exchange in New York. August gold settled Friday at $469.30 a troy
ounce compared with $456; July silver advanced to $7.27 a troy
ounce from $6.75.
   Energy futures were mixed on the New York Mercantile Exchange.
   West Texas Intermediate crude oil for July delivery rose to
$17.50 a barrel from $17.43; July heating oil was at 47.13 cents a
gallon compared with 47.04 cents; and July heating oil slipped to
50.89 cents a gallon from 52.55 cents.
